The '''1190s BC''' is a [[List of decades|decade]] which lasted from 1199 BC to 1190 BC.
{{Decadebox BC|119}}
==Events and trends==
* [[1197 BC]]—The beginning of the first period ([[1197 BC]]–[[982 BC]]) according to [[Sau Yung]]'s concept of the [[I Ching]] and history.
* [[1194 BC]]—The beginning of the legendary [[Trojan War]].
* [[1192 BC]]—[[Wu Ding]] [[Monarch|king]] of [[Shang Dynasty]] died.
* [[1191 BC]]—[[Menestheus]], legendary [[King of Athens]], dies during the [[Trojan War]] after a reign of 23 years and is succeeded by his nephew [[Demophon of Athens|Demophon]], a son of [[Theseus]]. Other accounts place his death a decade later and shortly after the [[Trojan War]] (see [[1180s BC]]).

==Significant people==
* [[Amenemses]], [[Pharaoh]] of the [[Nineteenth Dynasty]] of [[Egypt]] ([[1202 BC]]–1199 BC)

