The '''1740s BC''' was a decade lasting from January 1, 1749 BC to December 31, 1740 BC.

==Events and trends==
* 1749 BC–[[Samsu-iluna]] succeeds [[Hammurabi]] as king of [[Babylonia|Babylon]]. However, his rule is not very effective, and [[Mesopotamia]] endures turmoil during his reign.
* c. 1740 BC–[[Akkad (city)|Akkadian]]-[[Assyria]]n governor [[Puzur-Sin]] drives the [[Babylonia]]ns and [[Amorite]]s into the north, out of the land of [[Assyria]].

==Significant people==
* [[Rim-Sin I]], ruler of the Middle Eastern city-state of [[Larsa]] since 1758 BC
* [[Samsu-iluna]], king of [[Babylonia|Babylon]]

